HEADWORD: Frangulinic
<hw>Fran`gu*lin"ic</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining
to, or drived from, frangulin, or a species (<spn>Rhamnus
Frangula</spn>) of the buckthorn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Frangulinic acid</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a
yellow crystalline substance, resembling alizarin, and obtained by the
decomposition of frangulin.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frangulin</ent>⟦br⟧
